CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 5, 1966, pg. 2B reads: "Mr. and MRs. Charles Wilkins...Harris photo." "Portion of accompanying article reads: "Miss Rachael Pressley was married this fall in brilliant rites held in Park Place AME Church, Homestead, to Charles Wilkins Rev. Churchill Carter performed the ceremony.  A colorful garden reception followed the nuptials at the home of the bride, on Garfield Avenue, West Mifflin.  The bride is the daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Van Pressley."
TitMainTitle: Bride Rachael Pressley Wilkins wearing eyeglasses and veil with crown headpiece, and groom Charles Wilkins, standing by four tiered cake with swan decoration on lawn of Mr. and Mrs. Van Pressley home, Garfield Avenue, West Mifflin
